SIMPLE: swelling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swelling
<hw>Swell"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of that which
swells; <as>as, the <ex>swelling</ex> of rivers in spring; the
<ex>swelling</ex> of the breast with pride.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rise to the <qex>swelling</qex> of the voiceless sea.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A protuberance; a prominence</def>; especially
<fld>(Med.)</fld>, <def>an unnatural prominence or protuberance; <as>as,
a scrofulous <ex>swelling</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The superficies of such plates are not even, but have many
cavities and <qex>swellings</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir I.
Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swellish</ent>⟦br⟧
